Why Restraint Matters

Historically, disciplined traditions (knighthood, martial arts, military codes) emphasize a similar sequence:

observe fully
understand deeply
act deliberately

Action without observation leads to mistakes.
Observation without action leads to stagnation.

The balance is the skill.

